<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-755-466  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 755 466.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Publish!andP;  Sept 1990 v5 n9 p58(5).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Handheld scanners. (Hardware Review) (includes related article onshades of gray) (evaluation)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Aaland, Mikkel.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Handheld scanners have become more sophisticated.andP;  A gray-scalescanner is sufficient for digitizing photographs in image databases.andP;  Color scanners work for on-screen presentations.andP;  Bothkinds can serve as 'for position only' holders for illustrationsfor high-end publishing operations.andP;  They are not appropriate forusers who want production-quality scans.andP;  NCL's ClearScan Color,$795 for the Macintosh and IBM PC, scans 256 colors at a singlepass.andP;  The software permits color correction.andP;  The image must beless than 2.5 inches across, but several images can be pastedtogether.andP;  Hico's A4 Color Scanning System, $699 for the IBM PC,permits the user to change the color of a scanned image.andP;  SharpJX-100, $995 for the Macintosh and IBM PC, functions like aminiature flatbed scanner.andP;  It sits on top of the image and takesthree passes, scanning more evenly than the human hand can.andP;  Itsimages contain 262,144 colors.andP;  The JX-100 produces the bestresults for a thousand dollars, but it is not easy to use.andO;Niscan/GS, $369 for the IBM PC, is a true gray-scale scanner thatregisters 62 levels of gray at resolutions up to 400 dots perinch.andP;  Any of these scanners can fill a user's needs providedproduction-quality grays and color are not required.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   NCL America Computer Products Inc. (products)Hico Corporation of America (products)Sharp Electronics Corp. (products)NISCA Inc. (products).andO;Product:   NCL ClearScan Color (Scanning device)Hico A4 Color Scanning System (Scanning device)Sharp JX-100 (Scanning device)Niscan Niscan/GS (Scanning device).andO;Topic:     ScanningEvaluationImage GenerationDesktop Publishing.andO;Feature:   illustrationtablephotograph.andO;Caption:   Scanners at a glance. (table)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>